Cape Town â€“ Unicef has confirmed that the decomposed female body found on Table Mountain on Tuesday is that of Charlotte Nikoi. "We learned with great sadness that the remains of our colleague Charlotte (Nana Yaa) Nikoi have been found. All of us at Unicef are deeply saddened by this news and express our personal sympathies to her family. "Nana Yaa was a committed colleague who devoted the past 18 years of her life to the work and values of the United Nations. Her warmth and steadfast support will be missed by all those who knew her." Najwa Mikki spokesperson for Unicef said. Nikoi went missing on March 21 after she had gone hiking with her family. It was supposed to be their last day in Cape Town before leaving for Johannesburg.  marvin.charles@inl.co.za  IOL